items.sentence: I don't think you need to tell Tom what needs to be done.
I don't think you need to tell Tom what Mary plans to do.
I don't think we should tell Tom what Mary did yesterday.
I suspect that Tom went to Boston last weekend with Mary.
I suspect that Tom and Mary want us to help them do that.
Tom's teacher suspected that Tom had cheated on the test.
I don't think that either Tom or Mary will do that today.
I don't think that I know the girl that's talking to Tom.
I don't think that I ever knew what Tom did for a living.
I don't think that I can do that any better than Tom can.
